    "description": "ODAM (Open Data for Access and Mining) is an Experiment Data Table Management System (EDTMS) that implements a simple way to make research data broadly accessible and fully available for reuse, including by script languages such as R and Python. The main purpose is to make a dataset accessible online with minimal effort from the data provider, and to allow any data scientists or researchers to be able to explore the dataset and then extract a subpart or the totality of the data according to their needs.",
